Witnesses testified that Alvarez doused his Jeep Cherokee with gasoline, then abandoned it on the railroad tracks near Glendale, where it triggered a chain reaction crash involving two Metrolink trains and a rail car.
"The defendant placed a 4000 pound Molotov cocktail on the train tracks," prosecutor Alan Jackson said.
