Alvarez's attorney, Eric Chase, maintains his client was despondent over the breakup of his marriage and had planned to kill himself but not anyone else when he parked on the tracks.
"The gasoline simply assured that death would be quicker and more painless," said Chase, who claimed that his client tried to drive his Jeep off the tracks but got stuck.
