Hamas, which has improving relations with Cairo, may not want to embarrass Egypt in this way, said Oded Granot, a commentator on Arab affairs.
He suggested that al Qaida, an offshoot or an Egyptian radical group might be responsible.
In November 2002, attackers drove a car bomb into a resort hotel popular with Israelis in Mombasa, Kenya, killing 12, and fired missiles at an Israeli charter jet, which only narrowly missed their target.
