British Columbia Supreme Court Justice Ian Josephson said the prosecution's witnesses were not credible.
Josephson found Ripudaman Singh Malik, 58, and Ajaib Singh Bagri, 55, not guilty on all eight charges each man faced, including first degree murder and conspiracy to commit murder.
