In addition, key witnesses offered vague and contradictory recollections, and key evidence is circumstantial.
Both defendants Ripudaman Singh Malik, a 57 year old millionaire real estate entrepreneur, and Ajaib Singh Bagri, a 56 year old sawmill worker and Sikh preacher pleaded not guilty to charges of first degree murder and conspiracy in the bombing of the jet, Air India Flight 182 en route from Toronto and Montreal to India, on June 23, 1985.
